---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const pageTitle = "Community";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} mainClass="community-main">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Getting Started -->
    <section id="getting-started">
      <h1>Community</h1>
      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <p>
        The Universal Viewer is an open-source project that thrives on community
        collaboration. There are a number of ways to get involved — a great
        place to start is joining our <a
          href="https://universalviewer.slack.com">Slack channel</a
        > and connecting with other community members.
      </p>
      <p>
        A monthly community call is held on the first Thursday of each month and
        is open to all. These calls provide an opportunity to discuss and
        advance UV related topics, troubleshoot any technical issues, and
        connect with other users of the Universal Viewer.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our <a
          href="https://github.com/UniversalViewer/universalviewer?tab=readme-ov-file#-contributing-and-giving-feedback"
          >contributing guide</a
        > tells you how to run, modify and contribute to the software. Further information
        can be found in our online documentation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Community Sprints -->
    <section id="community-sprints">
      <h2>Community Sprints</h2>
      <p>
        Our community sprint programme is central to Universal Viewer
        development, helping to keep the project sustainable and closely aligned
        with user needs. Anyone is welcome to join these collaborative
        development efforts, regardless of technical skill. Upcoming sprints are
        listed on our <a href="/events">events page</a>, and you are welcome to
        reach out on <a href="https://universalviewer.slack.com">Slack</a> or join
        a community call for more information on how you can contribute.
      </p>

      <div class="community-links">
        <ul>
            <li>        <a href="/events" class="community-link">View upcoming events</a>
</li>
            <li>        <a href="/contact" class="community-link">Contact us</a>
</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="calendar-embed">
        <iframe
          src="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/embed?height=600&wkst=1&ctz=Europe%2FLondon&showPrint=0&showTitle=0&showTabs=0&showCalendars=0&src=dW5pdmVyc2Fsdmlld2VyYXBwQGdtYWlsLmNvbQ&color=%239e69af"
          style="border:solid 1px #777"
          width="800"
          height="600"
          frameborder="0"
          scrolling="no"></iframe>
      </div>

      <div class="social-links">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/UniversalViewer/universalviewer"
          class="social-link"
          aria-label="GitHub"
        >
          Github logo
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://universalviewer.slack.com"
          class="social-link"
          aria-label="Slack"
        >
          Slack logo
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://bsky.app/profile/universalviewer.io"
          class="social-link"
          aria-label="Bluesky"
        >
          BlueSky logo
        </a>
        <a href="https://glammr.us/@universalviewer" class="social-link" aria-label="Mastodon">
          Mastodon logo
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Steering Group -->
    <section id="steering-group">
      <h2>Steering Group</h2>
      <p>
        The role of the Steering Group is to provide a unified strategic
        direction and sustainability to the UV Community and to allocate
        <a href="https://opencollective.com/universalviewer">Open Collective</a>
        funds as appropriate.
      </p>
      <p>The group's responsibilities include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          develop value proposition and a formal inter-institutional roadmap for
          Universal Viewer development
        </li>
        <li>ensure sustainability to allow shared ownership and diversity</li>
        <li>
          setting priorities for the allocation of the Open Collective funds
          received
        </li>
        <li>discussing development requests received through user stories</li>
        <li>
          discussing developments resulting from projects funded outside of the
          OC
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Who are the Steering Group members?</h3>
      <p>
        Membership is currently restricted to those representatives of
        institutions contributing to the
        <a href="https://opencollective.com/universalviewer"
          >Open Collective UV fund</a
        >
        but welcomes new members at all times.
      </p>

      <div class="logos-grid" id="steering-logos">
        <a href="https://www.library.wales" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/llgc-logo.png" alt="National Library of Wales" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.bl.uk" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/330px-BritishLibrary.png"
            alt="British Library"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://library.villanova.edu" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/villanova-TRANSPARENT.png"
            alt="Falvey Library, Villanova University"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.tind.io" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/TIND-logo.png" alt="TIND" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://library.princeton.edu" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/princeton university logo.png"
            alt="Princeton University"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://library.ucla.edu" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/ucls-library.png" alt="UCLA Library" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/library/" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/uni-st-andrews-standard-vertical-black.png"
            alt="University of St Andrews"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://digirati.com" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/digirati-logo.png" alt="Digirati" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://mnemoscene.io" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/mnemoscene logo.jfif" alt="Mnemoscene" />
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contributors -->
    <section id="contributors">
      <h2>Thank you to our contributors</h2>
      <p>
        The Universal Viewer evolves through community input and we gratefully
        acknowledge the contributors and institutions whose support drives the
        project forward. Their collaboration and commitment make ongoing
        development and sustainability possible.
      </p>

      <div class="logos-grid" id="contributors-logos">
        <a href="https://www.britishonlinearchives.com" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/british online archives logo.png"
            alt="British Online Archives"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.nls.uk" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/National_Library_of_Scotland_logo.svg.png"
            alt="National Library of Scotland"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.notch8.com" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/Notch8_Color.avif" alt="Notch8" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.peoplescollection.wales" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/pcw.jpg" alt="People's Collection Wales" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.cogapp.com" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/Cogapp_Logo_lg_black.png" alt="Cogapp" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.vam.ac.uk" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/V&A.png" alt="Victoria & Albert Museum" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://www.riksarkivet.se" class="logo-item">
          <img
            src="/img/logos/Riksarkivet-swedish archives-TRANSPARENT.png"
            alt="Riksarkivet"
          />
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/Geoffsc" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/geoff.jpeg" alt="Geoff Scholl" />
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/staceyred" class="logo-item">
          <img src="/img/logos/stacey.jpeg" alt="Stacey Redick" />
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script is:inline>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    ["steering-logos", "contributors-logos"].forEach((id) => {
      const grid = document.getElementById(id);
      if (!grid) return;
      const items = Array.from(grid.children);
      items.sort(() => Math.random() - 0.5);
      items.forEach((item) => grid.appendChild(item));
    });
  });
</script>
